Solution Steps:

1. In Burp Repeater, request any non-existent path:
   GET /random
2. Confirm that the requested path is reflected in the error message.
3. Replace the path with the XSS payload:
   GET /random</p><script>alert(1)</script><p>foo
4. Poison the cache using this request.
5. Immediately load the same URL in the browser and verify that alert(1) is executed due to cache normalization.
6. Re-poison the cache.
7. Go back to the lab and click Deliver link to victim.
8. Submit the malicious URL.
9. The lab is solved when the victim visits the cached malicious URL.
